    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <head>59. National Security Action Memorandum No. 114<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d59fn0">Source: <persName>Kennedy</persName> Library, National
                        Security Files, Meetings and Memoranda Series, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                            >NSAM</gloss> 114. Secret. Copies were sent to <persName
                            corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_KRF1"
                            >Robert Kennedy</persName>, Director of the Bureau of the Budget
                            <persName corresp="#p_BDE1">Bell</persName>, Allen Dulles, and General
                            <persName corresp="#p_TMD1">Taylor</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-11-22">November 22, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Training for Friendly Police and Armed Forces in Counter-Insurgency,
                        Counter-Subversion, Riot Control and Related Matters</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has noted the reports received in response to <gloss
                        target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> No. 88<note n="1" xml:id="d59fn1">
                        <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> No. 88, addressed to the Secretary of
                        Defense, was a request for suggestions concerning U.S. training for Latin
                        American armed forces. (Ibid., <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>
                        88)</note> and requests that you make a continuing review in collaboration
                    with the Secretary of Defense and the Director of Central Intelligence, of the
                    over-all problem of United States support of friendly police and armed forces
                    and their training in riot control, counter-subversion, counter-insurgency, and
                    related operations. Such review should encompass general United States policies,
                    the assignment of departmental responsibilities, and the general size and scope
                    of United States programs. The general object should be to clarify and
                    strengthen these policies and programs while minimizing duplication and
                    conflicts.</p>
                <p>The President further requests that you give him periodic reports on the results
                    of the review, with recommendations of policy and courses of action. Latin
                    America should be the first area covered by the review.</p>
                <p>To the extent necessary, you should coordinate the review with National Security
                    Action Memorandum No. 56<note n="2" xml:id="d59fn2">
                        <ref target="#d33">Document 33</ref>.</note> on the evaluation of
                    paramilitary requirements, with the <gloss target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> and
                    foreign aid programs, and with previous Overseas Internal Security Program
                    reviews.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d59fn3">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                        signature.</note>
                </closer>
            </div>
